{{Infobox park | name = Elliott State Forest | photo = | photo_width = | photo_caption = Coos District | type = State forest, park | location = [[Coos County, Oregon]], [[United States]] | coords = | area = {{convert|93000|acre|km2}} | created = 1930 | operator = [[Oregon Department of Forestry]] | visitation_num = | status = | open = }} '''Elliott State Forest''' is a [[state forest]] in the [[Oregon Coast Range]] in [[Coos County, Oregon|Coos County]], between [[Coos Bay, Oregon|Coos Bay]] and [[Reedsport, Oregon|Reedsport]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Elliott State Forest Facts|url=http://www.oregon.gov/ODF/elliottstateforestfacts.shtml|publisher=[[Oregon Department of Forestry]]}}</ref> The first state forest established in [[Oregon]], it is named after the state's first state forester Francis Elliott.<ref>{{cite web|title=Elliott State Forest|url=http://www.oregon.gov/ODF/docs/2009_Backgrounder_Elliott_State_Forest.pdf|publisher=Oregon Department of Forestry}}</ref><ref name="wildlands">{{cite web|title=Elliott State Forest Background|url=http://www.cascwild.org/elliott.html|publisher=Cascadia Wildlands (cascwild.org)}}</ref>
